---
title: Cheesy Pork & Black Bean Bake with Lime Rice, Sour Cream & Tortillas
description: This big batch bean bake is ready to please a crowd! Seared ground pork, bell peppers, and black beans are simmered in our bold Tex-Mex-style spices. It's topped with a Mexican cheese blend, baked until piping hot and melty, then it’s straight to the table family style with warm tortillas and lime rice, plus sour cream and lime wedges to cool things off.

*This recipe is double the typical servings, providing 4 servings and 8 servings for a 2 person and 4 person box respectively.*

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/672112ab17d64dc2b9c19b35-6628b3f0.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/672112ab17d64dc2b9c19b35-en-US.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 1290 kcal
  fat: 60 g
  saturated fat: 25 g
  carbohydrates: 123 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 53 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1660 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheesy-pork-and-black-bean-bake-672112ab17d64dc2b9c19b35
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North American
---

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

In a #medium pot{} (large pot for 8 servings), combine @white rice{1%cup}, 1 1/2
cups water (2 1/2 cups for 8), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then
cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 6.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Halve, deseed, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1} crosswise into strips.
Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest
@lime{1} and quarter both (zest two limes and quarter all for 8 servings).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Tex-Mex paste{1}, @water{1/4%cup}, and
@sugar{1%tbsp} (1/2 cup water and 2 TBSP sugar for 8).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add bell pepper and cook, stirring, until softened and slightly browned,
~{2%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{20%oz}*, scallion whites, and @Fajita Spice Blend{2%tbsp};
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until
cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

Meanwhile, drain @black beans{2} (no need to rinse!).

Reduce heat under pan to medium low. Add beans and Tex-Mex sauce to pan. Stir to
combine. Cover and cook until liquid has slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.
Season with salt and pepper.

> For 8 servings, you may need to cook pork and beans in batches.

Transfer pork and beans to an #8-by-8-inch baking dish{} (9-by-13-inch baking
dish for 8 servings).

Sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1%cup} and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}. Bake,
uncovered, on middle rack until cheese is melted and bubbly, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wrap @flour tortillas{12} in damp #paper towels{}. Microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and juice from
@lime{1}(quartered) (eight wedges for 8 servings). Taste and season with salt
and additional lime juice if desired.

Sprinkle cheesy pork and black bean bake with scallion greens. Serve family
style with lime rice, tortillas, @sour cream{6%tbsp}, and remaining lime wedges
on the side.